{"id": "EUVD-2024-44569", "enisaUuid": "5c75fb9f-1738-3cfc-b586-88fef0e15ee8", "description": "In the Linux kernel, the following vulnerability has been resolved:\n\nsfc: Don't invoke xdp_do_flush() from netpoll.\n\nYury reported a crash in the sfc driver originated from\nnetpoll_send_udp(). The netconsole sends a message and then netpoll\ninvokes the driver's NAPI function with a budget of zero. It is\ndedicated to allow driver to free TX resources, that it may have used\nwhile sending the packet.\n\nIn the netpoll case the driver invokes xdp_do_flush() unconditionally,\nleading to crash because bpf_net_context was never assigned.\n\nInvoke xdp_do_flush() only if budget is not zero.", "datePublished": "2024-11-05T17:04:57", "dateUpdated": "2025-10-01T20:27:19", "baseScore": 5.5, "baseScoreVersion": "3.1", "baseScoreVector": "CVSS:3.1/AV:L/AC:L/PR:L/UI:N/S:U/C:N/I:N/A:H", "references": ["https://git.kernel.org/stable/c/65d4fc76d75c136744e67754d20feda609e7b793", "https://git.kernel.org/stable/c/55e802468e1d38dec8e25a2fdb6078d45b647e8c"], "aliases": ["CVE-2024-50094"], "assigner": "Linux", "epss": 0.03, "enisaIdProduct": [{"id": "0e208376-fbb9-35ff-bb35-777553234733", "product": {"name": "Linux"}, "product_version": "6.11"}, {"id": "1685ae2a-16b1-3741-a8ec-5d12761e159d", "product": {"name": "Linux"}, "product_version": "401cb7dae8130fd34eb84648e02ab4c506df7d5e <65d4fc76d75c136744e67754d20feda609e7b793"}, {"id": "3d637b53-87d4-3969-9cd5-6394ddba32b6", "product": {"name": "Linux"}, "product_version": "patch: 0"}, {"id": "62475b51-058f-36a9-8742-bd2f4188439b", "product": {"name": "Linux"}, "product_version": "401cb7dae8130fd34eb84648e02ab4c506df7d5e <55e802468e1d38dec8e25a2fdb6078d45b647e8c"}, {"id": "b78d42f7-be29-3160-b28c-b1e5f555a555", "product": {"name": "Linux"}, "product_version": "patch: 6.11.4"}, {"id": "e80e15b7-85e3-3d83-9c26-e4875de32101", "product": {"name": "Linux"}, "product_version": "patch: 6.12"}], "enisaIdVendor": [{"id": "56fcd695-8214-37c2-a150-86b3c